    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": ">the address passed as an argument could have a typo and then the result could be catastrophic\r\n\r\nThis is sometimes true, and I love the idea of using `msg.sender` as a safety mechanism, but it's not relevant for the case of `SplitPayment`, because the critical use of the address (the payment) has already passed. I think we can use that as a heuristic. When a typo in the address does not have critical consequences, we should use address arguments for maximum flexibility; otherwise we should use `msg.sender`.\r\n\r\n@nventuro @elopio How does this sound?",
