    "created_at": "2018-09-04T23:10:34Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-09-04T23:11:14Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@ddbit The use case you presented is interesting, although I have a hard time picturing the actual implementation for such dividends. However, I think this argument is not strong enough when compared to the potential enabled by allowing anyone to release funds or trigger pending payments. It means that you can set any address as the beneficiary without imposing constraints on it (e.g. being able to call `release` on a specific contract), and this leads to great composability.\r\n\r\nIf someone really needs to control when a `release` is triggered, they can opt-in to this behavior by using a contract as the beneficiary that rejects funds unless a given condition is satisfied (such as being the originator of the release).",
